Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
gui_get_objects_from_schematic(25.10)    gui_get_objects_from_schematic(25.10)

Name
       gui_get_objects_from_schematic - Gets the names of all or the specified
       type of objects from the current (active) or specified schematic view

Syntax
       gui_get_objects_from_schematic

       [-name <string>]

       -type {all insts modules nets ports}

       Gets the names of all or the specified type of objects from the current
       (active) or specified schematic view.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the gui_get_objects_from_schematic
              command.

              For  a detailed description of the command, use the man command:
              man gui_get_objects_from_schematic.

       -name <string>
              Specifies the name of the schematic view from which objects need
              to be returned. If -name is not specified, returns objects  from
              the current schematic view.

              You can use the gui_get_schematic command to get the name of the
              current or all open schematics.

       -type {all insts modules nets ports}
              Specifies  the  type  of  the  objects to be returned. If all is
              specified, returns the name of all objects from the  current  or
              specified schematic view.

Examples
              * The  following  command returns the instances from the current
                schematic:

                > gui_get_objects_from_schematic -type insts

                Sample output:

                ram1/subram02_lower/TESTACT_INST_PERIWD-
                SRAM001PAA512W27C3/FE_OFC1329_q02_8_  ram1/subram02_lower/TES-
                TACT_INST_PERIWDSRAM001PAA512W27C3/FE_OFC1326_q02_10_
                ram1/subram02_lower/TESTACT_INST_PERIWDSRAM001PAA512W27C3/TES-
                TACT_WSRAM/assignbuf_709853           ram1/subram02_lower/TES-
                TACT_INST_PERIWDSRAM001PAA512W27C3/U170              ram1/sub-
                ram02_lower/TESTACT_INST_PERIWDSRAM001PAA512W27C3/U182
                ram1/subram02_lower/TESTACT_INST_PERIWDSRAM001PAA512W27C3/U184
                ram1/subram02_lower/TESTACT_INST_PERIWDSRAM001PAA512W27C3/U187
                ram1/subram02_lower/TESTACT_INST_PERIWDSRAM001PAA512W27C3/U189
                ram1/subram02_lower/TESTACT_INST_PERIWDSRAM001PAA512W27C3/U202

              * The following command returns the nets from the schematic view
                named W0:

                > gui_get_objects_from_schematic -name W0 -type nets

                Sample output:

                ram1/subram02_lower/TESTACT_INST_PERIWDSRAM001PAA512W27C3/n7
                ram1/subram02_lower/TESTACT_INST_PERIWD-
                SRAM001PAA512W27C3/tpo_a_9_ VSS VDD

